   Indeed, since `⨅ i, I i ≤ I i`, there is a natural map `R ⧸ ⨅ i, I i →+* R ⧸ I i`. 

   Moreover, this map is the same as `Quotient.mk (I i)` composed with `Quotient.mk (⨅ i, I i)` because `x + ⨅ i, I i ↦ x + I i`. 

   (Check this: `(x + ⨅ i, I i) ↦ (x + I i)` because `⨅ i, I i ≤ I i`, and `Quotient.mk (I i) x = x + I i`.)

   Thus, the Chinese map can also be defined as `(Quotient.mk (⨅ i, I i)) x ↦ ( (Quotient.mk (I i)) x )` (but this is exactly what's in the Lean definition, since in Lean `(chineseMap x) i = (Quotient.mk (I i)) x`).

